Package eu.profinit.manta.dataflow.generator.modeling.common.connections

Interface DatabaseConnector

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    DatabaseConnectorImpl
    public interface DatabaseConnector
    Provides access to database dictionary nodes by their description. Also disposes of fallback node creation methods for the case, when the described node counterpart is unreachable.
    Author:
    ddrobny

      • createTableNode

        eu.profinit.manta.dataflow.model.Node createTableNode​(eu.profinit.manta.connector.common.connections.Connection connection,
                                                      NodeMetadata table,
                                                      java.lang.String dbName,
                                                      java.lang.String schemaName,
                                                      eu.profinit.manta.dataflow.model.Graph graph)
        Attempts to retrieve a node for a server, database, schema and table hierarchy based on the passed values using the dictionary. If the retrieval is successful, the hierarchy is added to the output graph.
        Parameters:
        connection - connection attributes. Must be non-null.
        table - details of the created table. Its name must be non-blank.
        dbName - name of the table's database or null if it is not known.
        schemaName - name of the table's schema or null if it is not known.
        graph - the output graph.
        Returns:
        Newly created node for the table or null if the retrieval was not successful.
